This paper deals with the detection and analysis of malware communication over TLS, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The paper also uses machine learning techniques to classify malware families, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper discusses the use of rules and classifiers, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of large datasets, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
